        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 4:41PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 440 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Centralhatchee, or 9
miles north of Franklin, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Newnan, Carrollton, Bremen, Palmetto, Bowdon, Mount Zion, Whitesburg,
Waco, Ephesus, Centralhatchee, Roopville, Plant Yates, Seaton Lake,
Dunaway Gardens, Clem, Abilene, John Tanner State Park, Blackjack
Mountain, Madras, and Byers Crossroads.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
